727687f-a.title: Queens: Pitkin Avenue - 88th Street
727687f-a.text:
Pitkin Avenue, south side, at about 88th Street, showing
the IIsaac Doxsey Wouse. Phil Uhl was the last owner who sold
it to M. Silverman, a land developer. Pitkin Avenue, here, is
the old South Noad.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection  -----1895
MAY BE REPRODUCED

727688f-a.title: Queens: Pitkin Avenue - 88th Street
727688f-a.text:
Pitkin Ave. (O1d South Road), north side, in 88th Street,
showing a rear view of the William Doxsey house. Shown also is
the well house. If the house were standing in 1938 it would be just
south of the Blake Avenue Street line in 88th Street.
1922.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
